{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"432ece27-e847-42dd-bce1-eedfcb1a6908","content":"On macOS, when a NativeAOT app crashes, look in these locations:\n\n1. **Apple Crash Reports** — macOS automatically generates `.ips` crash reports:\n   ```\n   ~/Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/\n   /Library/Logs/DiagnosticReports/\n   ```\n   Files are named like `YourApp_YYYY-MM-DD-HHMMSS_machinename.ips`.\n\n2. **Core dumps** — if enabled:\n   ```bash\n   ulimit -c unlimited   # enable before running\n   ```\n   Cores land in `/cores/core.<pid>`.\n\n3. **Console.app** — open it and check **Crash Reports** in the sidebar for a formatted view of the `.ips` files.\n\nThe `.ips` crash report will contain the faulting thread, stack trace, and signal info — usually enough to start debugging without `createdump`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"f8f78257-e4df-41b4-93b6-929be67fc81c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about finding crash dumps/reports for a NativeAOT app on macOS when `createdump` isn't available. This is a knowledge question — no tools needed.","outputTokens":278,"requestId":"AC11:3AFCA9:146828E:16D7B3C:6A06712A"},"id":"d522975f-f845-4b22-905b-e8f7b5855611","timestamp":"2026-05-15T01:04:49.475Z","parentId":"41bdc68e-cb7a-4e59-ae03-35cc1432e72f"}
